name: DeployResult
description: Represents the results of a metadata deployment.

canceledby.name: canceledBy
canceledby.description: ID of the user who canceled the queued deployment.

canceledbyname.name: canceledByName
canceledbyname.description: Full name of the user who canceled the queued deployment.

checkonly.name: checkOnly
checkonly.description: Indicates whether the deployment checked only the validity of the deployed files without making changes in the org. A check-only deployment does not deploy components or change the org in any way.

completeddate.name: completedDate
completeddate.description: Date and time for when the deployment process ended.

createdby.name: createdBy
createdby.description: ID of the user who created the deployment job.

createdbyname.name: createdByName
createdbyname.description: Full name of the user who created the deployment job.

createddate.name: createdDate
createddate.description: Date and time the deployment job was first queued.

details.name: details
details.description: Provides the details for components in a completed deployment.

done.name: done
done.description: Indicates whether Salesforce finished processing the deployment.

errormessage.name: errorMessage
errormessage.description: Message corresponding to the values in the errorStatusCode property, if any.

errorstatuscode.name: errorStatusCode
errorstatuscode.description: If an error occurs during deployment, a status code is returned. The message corresponding to the status code is returned in the errorMessagefield property.

ignorewarnings.name: ignoreWarnings
ignorewarnings.description: Specifies whether a deployment continues, even if the deployment generates warnings.

lastmodifieddate.name: lastModifiedDate
lastmodifieddate.description: Date and time of the last update for the deployment process.

messages.name: messages
messages.description: A list of all the detail messages for a deployment.

numbercomponenterrors.name: numberComponentErrors
numbercomponenterrors.description: The number of components that generated errors during the deployment.

numbercomponentsdeployed.name: numberComponentsDeployed
numbercomponentsdeployed.description: The number of components deployed in the deployment process. Use this value with the numberComponentsTotal property to get an estimate of the deployment’s progress.

numbercomponentstotal.name: numberComponentsTotal
numbercomponentstotal.description: The total number of components in the deployment. Use this value with the numberComponentsDeployed property to get an estimate of the deployment’s progress.

rollbackonerror.name: rollbackOnError
rollbackonerror.description: Indicates whether any failure causes a complete rollback (true) or not (false) of the deployment.

startdate.name: startDate
startdate.description: Date and time the deployment process began.

statedetail.name: stateDetail
statedetail.description: Indicates which component is being deployed.

status.name: status
status.description: Indicates the current state of the deployment.

success.name: success
success.description: Indicates whether the deployment was successful (true) or not (false).

clone().name: clone
clone().description: Makes a duplicate copy of the Metadata.DeployResult.
